### Resource: Comment

* **Name:** `Comment`
* **Description:** A Comment resource represents a single note, or comment, in a discussion thread.
* **Type URI:** [`http://open-services.net/ns/core#Comment`](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Comment)

| **Prefixed Name** | **Occurs** | **Read-only** | **Value-type** | **Representation** | **Range** | **Description** 
| ----------------- | ---------- | ------------- | -------------- | ------------------ | --------- | ----------------- 
| Properties  |||||||
| [`dcterms:identifier`](http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier) | [Exactly-one](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Exactly-one) | true | [String](http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string) | N/A | N/A | A service defined identifier. 
| [`dcterms:creator`](http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator) | [Exactly-one](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Exactly-one) | true | [Resource](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource) | [Either](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Either) | [`oslc:Any`](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Any)  | The person who created the comment. It is likely that the target resource will be a [[OSLCCoreSpecAppendixA#foaf_Person_Resource][ =foaf:Person= ]] but that is not necessarily the case. 
| [`dcterms:title`](http://purl.org/dc/terms/title) | [Zero-or-one](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-one) | Unspecified | [XMLLiteral](http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral) | N/A | N/A | A brief title for the comment. *SHOULD* include only content that is valid and suitable inside an XHTML &lt;span&gt; element. 
| [`dcterms:created`](http://purl.org/dc/terms/created) | [Exactly-one](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Exactly-one) | true | [DateTime](http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime) | N/A | N/A | When the comment resource was created. 
| [`dcterms:description`](http://purl.org/dc/terms/description) | [Exactly-one](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Exactly-one) | Unspecified | [XMLLiteral](http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral) | N/A | N/A | Details or body of the comment. *SHOULD* include only content that is valid and suitable inside an XHTML &lt;div&gt; element. 
| [`oslc:partOfDiscussion`](http://open-services.net/ns/core#partOfDiscussion) | [Exactly-one](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Exactly-one) | Unspecified | [Resource](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource) | [Reference](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Reference) | [`oslc:Any`](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Any)  | Reference to owning Discussion resource. It is likely that the target resource will be an [`oslc:Discussion`](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Discussion)  but that is not necessarily the case. 
| [`oslc:inReplyTo`](http://open-services.net/ns/core#inReplyTo) | [Zero-or-one](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Zero-or-one) | Unspecified | [Resource](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Resource) | [Reference](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Reference) | [`oslc:Any`](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Any)  | Reference to comment this comment is in reply to. It is likely that the target resource will be an [`oslc:Comment`](http://open-services.net/ns/core#Comment)  but that is not necessarily the case. 
